<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>dead ship • death ship</xh5><p> <i>dead ship</i>—(Nautical) a ship without power: They saw no movement, no living or dead person, no sign of violence; nothing, but the ordered emptiness of a darkened and <u>dead ship</u>.</p><p><i>death ship—</i>a ship deliberately wrecked so that the owners can collect insurance money: He is forced to join the crew of a “<u>death ship</u>” ... betrothed to the ocean floor in exchange for insurance money.</p><p> <i>See also: ghost ship</i> / <i>ghost train</i>.</p> </entry>
